"If this university community is going to be able to have the impact it needs to have, central to the mission has to be this idea of DEI. Not as a favor to anybody. It's a superpower." @VanJones68 #UMichDEI

"We're developing a capacity for people to at least work across difference. To recognize the battleground and deal with that effectively, but never lose sight of the common ground." @VanJones68 #UMichDEI

We have more problems to solve in the new century than we've ever had before and yet we continue on this path of sending people out who can't work in problem solving teams because they can't talk to someone who looks different. -@VanJones68 #UMichDEI
"You've got to learn how to work across idealogical lines, racial lines, to get something done." @VanJones68 #UMichDEI
"I have learned that cognitive diversity, racial diversity, gender diversity, idealogical diversity, viewpoint diversity, are strengths, not weaknesses." @VanJones68 #UMichDEI

"I look forward to joining you as this important work continues beyond the initial five-year strategic plan. And as I begin my second five-year term as president, DEI will remain a focus and will continue to throughout my presidency." @DrMarkSchlissel #UMichDEI
"Thank you to everyone who is advancing diversity, equity, and inclusion at U-M." @DrMarkSchlissel #UMichDEI
"Our achievements thus far are a direct result of so many members of our community joining together: to not only advance our values, but to live them." @DrMarkSchlissel #UMichDEI
"In turn, this means that there is also common ground upon which we can build more effective, respectful, and productive relationships across our differences." @DrRobSellers #UMichDEI

"We all hold identities in which we are privileged as well as identities in which we have been marginalized or underrepresented. This is not to intimate that all forms of privilege and marginalization are the same. But it means we all have some common experiences." @DrRobSellers

"Our month-long DEI summit provides an opportunity to acknowledge our progress thus far in the five year DEI plan implementation, as well as recommit ourselves to address the challenges we still face in creating a more diverse, equitable, and inclusive community" @DrRobSellers

A new study by U-M researchers found that negative portrayals of Muslim Americans in media can have adverse effects on how Muslims view themselves as citizens and their trust in the government. http://myumi.ch/6wY7N
Join President @DrMarkSchlissel and the U-M Commission on Carbon Neutrality at a special public session to discuss our path toward carbon neutrality Tuesday, April 9th. http://myumi.ch/LBOWl

Happy #Holi Wolverines! Want to celebrate the festival of colors? Don’t miss U-M’s Indian Student Association and Hindu Students Council’s special Holi festival March 31 at Palmer field. RSVP at: http://myumi.ch/a0Kyl

As we celebrate professors Rosina Bierbaum and Joseph Ryan for their public engagement efforts, hear from previous award recipients on what recognition for their leadership means to them. Learn more about public engagement at U-M here: http://myumi.ch/L4n1N #UMichImpact

From searching for abandoned instruments to collaborating with community partners, Victoria Bigelow from @UMichEducation has made it her mission to bring music to Flint students. #URecord http://myumi.ch/aG4Rz

Babies with Down syndrome typically start walking much later than other children. For years, @UMKines researchers have been helping children with Down syndrome develop their walking skills with a miniature treadmill therapy program. #WorldDownSyndromeDay http://myumi.ch/L4dvR

Former @chicagotribune chairman and CEO and U-M alum John W. Madigan and his wife Holly recently gifted more than $300,000 to the @michigandaily in honor of @amlwhere, the Tribune’s first female editor and fellow alum. http://myumi.ch/6jXV3

In this episode of Michigan Minds, @UMSocialWork researchers @DrShannaK and Ashley Lacombe-Duncan discuss how they’re studying transgender experiences in healthcare to help improve treatment. http://myumi.ch/JmWBz #UMichImpact

When seasons change, our bodies know to react accordingly—making us perceive the same thermometer reading differently at different times of the year. Read about how your body acclimates to the changing seasons: http://myumi.ch/6QgGe #FirstDayOfSpring

With 63 volunteers, U-M ranks 4th among large universities for producing the most Peace Corps volunteers in 2019. Since the agency’s creation in 1961, U-M has had 2,734 alumni serve across the globe. http://myumi.ch/LRkZD
Join UMDC tomorrow for its Eye on Detroit Series and hear U-M experts discuss what makes a great brand, whether personal or professional. http://myumi.ch/Lr1l7 #UMichDetroit #EngagedMichigan

A new live-imaging technique developed by U-M researchers makes it possible to view cell repair to the epithelial barriers coating our organs and protecting us from bacteria, viruses, and other disease-causing elements. http://myumi.ch/a8QOn
"Hello, @umichmedicine? Yes, it’s an emergency. It’s official, we’ve got Spring Fever!" #FirstDayofSpring

Sometimes the only way to go is down. When @UMichLaw's library hit capacity, and books started to pile up the underground library was born through an architect’s vision and a Law School dean’s perseverance. http://myumi.ch/Lr1BZ
How could plastics be harming your health? @UMichSPH professor John Meeker talked with @Salon about the need for more research into microplaslic toxicity and exposure levels. http://myumi.ch/L3Kny

U-M researchers are part of a new, federally funded effort to understand and prevent the toxic algal blooms that plague portions of the Great Lakes and impact freshwater sources around the world. http://myumi.ch/aApnW #UMichImpact
#UMBiosciences
Many @umichLSA students jump-start their professional education by learning about industries from LSA alumni. Here's how the LSA Opportunity Hub helps make the connections. http://myumi.ch/abwDK

Sara Ahbel-Rappe and Elena Gallo of @umichLSA and Annalisa Manera of @UMengineering have been elected to 3-year terms on @UMSACUA, the executive arm of U-M’s central faculty governance. http://myumi.ch/Jyz4R #URecord
Hey Katie! We actually have a cassette with this address in our archives at the @umichBentley. We'll work on getting that transcribed for you!
We're proud to call Cathy an alumna! We especially love this interview she did with the @michigandaily in 1984:
As part of the Michigan Union restoration project, Full Spectrum Stained Glass of Colon, MI, is working to fully restore the Union’s historic windows. http://myumi.ch/6xoPz @UMichUnions #URecord

Never stop learning, with #MichiganOnline. Faculty, staff, @UMichStudents, and @michiganalumni can access 130+ courses for free through Michigan Online! Explore a passion or learn new skills for your career at http://online.umich.edu #MichiganOnline #HereToLearn

Whether your dream is to bring a new product to market, develop a groundbreaking new app, or change the way an industry does business, you can find all the resources you need through @InnovateBlue. Learn more at: http://innovateblue.umich.edu

U-M is proud to collaborate with the city of Detroit's Health Department and Dr. Joneigh S. Khaldun to find solutions to community health challenges. Learn more in the #PovertySolutions Impact Report: http://myumi.ch/6eoE2

U-M’s National Poll on Healthy Aging is a recurring, nationally representative household survey launched in 2017 in partnership with AARP. Today, experts from @umichmedicine and @UM_IHPI will be discussing the latest poll in Lansing. #WolverineCaucus http://myumi.ch/6Qgyg
An associate professor at @UMichNursing is encouraging couples in South Africa to get tested for HIV through a couples counseling program called Uthando Lwethu, or “our love.” http://myumi.ch/6pVje

What does the future of work look like? Join us March 26 as Walmart USA President & CEO Greg Foran and Michigan government and community leaders discuss how to promote equity as the nature of work evolves. http://myumi.ch/LBO9B #PovertySolutions

.@umichPCAP will open its 24th Annual Exhibition of Art by Michigan Prisoners this Wednesday. The exhibit will highlight the work of 574 artists from 26 facilities in Michigan, and will feature 670 paintings, sculptures, and 3-D works. #UMichArts http://myumi.ch/JyzgR

U-M alum Philip Power and his wife Kathy have been instrumental in increasing awareness and appreciation for Inuit art. To inaugurate the new Power Family Program for Inuit Art, @ummamuseum will showcase 58 works from their collection of over 200 statues. http://myumi.ch/6jXBK
Alison Miller, associate professor at @UMichSPH, is researching stress reduction tools for parents to help them be “the best parent they can be to their child.” http://myumi.ch/aZqnq #UMichImpact
#UMichImpact

Taking action will help U-M reach our 2025 sustainability goals. Incorporate these tips by looking for recycling outlets around campus. Want a complete list of recyclables? http://myumi.ch/JN7y0 #PlanetBlue #RecycleMania

"Yes, we have challenges. Yes, the road ahead is difficult, but that cannot stop us. We have to move forward and we have to invite others to move forward and use their creativity, their innovation, their wherewithal to help." -@CFigueres #UMichTalks #ClimateAction
"We have to approach our challenges with optimism and stubbornness. We have to be optimistic, but we cannot afford to be naive." -@CFigueres #UMichTalks
"The question is not, are we moving in the right direction? The question is are we moving fast enough?" -@CFigueres #UMichTalks #ClimateAction

"There definitely is a legacy of fossil fuels in the power grids and transportation but we are moving exponentially toward a renewable world. We're on our way to an exciting future." -@CFigueres #UMichTalks

"We have started to chart a course to address the change. That is what my generation has done. The older generation had no idea what climate change was. Now, because of understanding, we have the full responsibility of addressing this challenge." -@CFigueres

"The decisions we're making now will decide the quality of life on this planet for the next 100 years. We're talking about investment and policy decisions today that will effect the quality of life for the next 100 years. That puts quite a bit of pressure on us." -@CFigueres

"I hope that the opportunity to hear from such an influential leader today inspires a sense of optimism about the challenges that lie ahead." -@DrMarkSchlissel welcomes @CFigueres to the stage. #UMichTalks #ClimateAction

.@CFigueres, architect of the Pairs Climate Agreement, is delivering the Peter M. Wege Lecture on Sustainability this evening in Hill Auditorium. Follow along for highlights from her discussion "No Victory Without Optimism: Advancing #ClimateAction in 2019 & Beyond." #UMichTalks

"We all need to do something. We all need to get in the fight, but that's going to look different for different people. I don't have a prescription for it." -Julia Putnam, Principal and writer #UMichMLK
"We can't ignore the kids in this conversation. They're going to teach us too." -Julia Putnam, Principal and writer

"Educational work has to be seen as revolutionary work. It is not reformist work. If you are not in the business of liberating people from systems of inequality and injustice, then you're not really in the business of educating." -@timjacobwise, Author and Scholar

"I'm hopeful in what I've seen and heard that here, there's an effort to not only do the draining and DE&I dialogue, but to ensure that these concepts are woven into selection criteria for hiring and promotion criteria." -@timjacobwise, Author and Scholar
"Instead of tinkering around the edges of public policy, changing some here and tinkering a bit there, we realize that we have to create a new machine." -@timjacobwise, Author and Scholar

"Unless and until we can get to that place that we see ourselves in the other and we see the others in ourselves, we will never create what Dr. King called the beloved community, a nation of justice, a world of justice." - @timjacobwise, Author and Scholar

"You don't have to specify that which is taken for granted. You don't have to specify the things that we all know to be true. You have to specify that which has been left out, that which has been ignored and neglected." -@timjacobwise, Author and Scholar

"Our method of resistance is to hold ourselves and our children accountable to a clear mission and a vision of a sustainable planet that we all share with empathy, inclusion, collaboration, justice, and freedom!" -Julia Putnam, Principal and writer #UMichMLK

"Some say it's ridiculous to unravel things slowly. That we need to rip it all apart right now. Heartbreakingly the same arguments from 400 years ago about resistance remain today." -Julia Putnam, Principal and writer #UMichMLK

"Just as Dr. King stood in front of a multitude of people who made the movement, I stand as a representative of a community that has made it a point to love one another while holding ourselves accountable to our kids first." -Julia Putnam, Principal and writer #UMichMLK

"We're proud that U-M remains at the forefront of work that combats injustice in our nation's institutions. Combating injustice is part of our pedagogy. Our inclusive teaching initiative is improving our ability to more effectively teach all of our students." -@DrMarkSchlissel

"U-M students and scholars, for generations, have challenged our society through activism and groundbreaking research. In fact, this celebration is the product of campus activism in the mid and late 1980s." -@DrMarkSchlissel #UMichMLK

"The symposium theme of 'Unravel' gives us the important opportunity to question and examine not only the society we serve, but ourselves. It aligns with Dr. King's vision that 'human progress never rolls in on the wheels of inevitability.'" -@DrMarkSchlissel #UMichMLK
